
.ad l

.ll 72

.ce 1000
\fBdb.eval()\fR
.ce 0

.sp 2

.SH "NAME"
\fBNAME\fR
.sp 2
eval - According need to fill javaScript statement.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBSYNOPSIS\fR
.sp 2

.sp 2

.sp 2
db.eval(\fBcode\fR)
.SH "CATEGORY"
\fBCATEGORY\fR
.sp 2

.sp 2
Sequoiadb
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBDESCRIPTION\fR
.sp 2
According need to fill javaScript statement. Meanwhile you can a
stored procedure in the statement has been created good.
.sp 2
\fBcode (string)\fR
.br
         JavaScript statement or stored procedure to create a
         good function.
.sp 2
*  In accordance with the statement executed successfully return
   results. The return value can be directly assigned to another
   variable. Eg: \fBvar a = db.eval(' db.foo.bar'); a.find(); \fR
.sp 2
*  fails returns an error code and error message. Such as: \fB{
   "errmsg": "(nofile):1 ReferenceError: sum is not
   defined","retCode": -152 } \fR
.sp 2
*  Operation does not return before the end of the function
   execution. Dropouts terminated throughout the implementation,
   but the code has been executed will not be rolled back.
.sp 2
*  Customize the length of the return value of a certain limit,
   the reference SequoiaDB insert records maximum length.
.sp 2
*  Define the temporary support functions, such as: \fBdb.eval('
   function sum(x,y){return x+y;} sum(1,2)')\fR
.sp 2
*  Global db usage and createProcedure same.
.sp 2
\fBNote: \fRWhile all the output statement will be shielded, but
it is recommended not to join any print statements.
.SH "Examples"
\fBExamples\fR
.sp 2

.sp 2
Call a stored procedure function sum in the eval() method.
.sp 2
//Initial sum() method does not exist, return exception information.
.br
> var a = db.eval('sum(1,2)');
.br
{ "errmsg": "(nofile):1 ReferenceError: getCL is not defined
.br
", "retCode": -152 }
.br
(nofile):0 uncaught exception: -152
.br
//Initialization sum()
.br
>db.createProcedure(function sum(x,y){return x+y;})
.br
//Call the sum()
.br
>db.eval('sum(1,2)')
.br
3
.sp 2
Fill javaScript statement eval() method
.sp 2
>var rc = db.eval("db.foo.bar")
.br
>rc.find()
